Class CommandManager

      • parseCommand

        public boolean parseCommand(MessageReceiver caller,
                            java.lang.String command,
                            java.lang.String[] args)
        Performs a lookup for a command of the given name and executes it if found. Returns false if the command wasn't found or if the caller doesn't have the permission to run it.
        In Short: Use this to fire commands.
        Parameters:
        command - The command to run
        caller - The MessageReceiver to send messages back to (assumed to be the caller)
        args - The arguments to command (including command)
        Returns:
        true if command executed successfully, false otherwise

      • registerCommands

        public void registerCommands(CommandListener listener,
                             CommandOwner owner,
                             LocaleHelper translator,
                             boolean force)
                      throws CommandDependencyException
        Register your CommandListener. This will make all annotated commands available to CanaryMod and the help system. Sub Command relations can only be sorted out after availability. That means if you try to register a command that is a sub-command of something that is not registered yet, it will fail. So make sure you add commands in the correct order.
        Parameters:
        listener - the CommandListener
        owner - the CommandOwner
        translator - the LocaleHelper instance used in Translations
        force - true to override existing commands; false for not
        Throws:
        CommandDependencyException
